I had typed out my story, ready to share the mental abuse I endured from a toxic boss, but then I thought, why give her that satisfaction?

When I was laid off, I cried. Not because I was sad... but because it was finally OVER. I was free. And let me tell you—my first Monday unemployed? It felt incredible.

In January 2022, I started Spice Up Your Social. I loved the work I was doing there, so I decided to keep going, but this time, as my own boss (I know, so cliché 🥲).

From 2022 to 2024, I attended @csunorthridge to finish my Bachelor’s degree. (I dropped out of college and went back in 2020 at the age of 28).

I graduated at 32 and immediately started applying to Master’s programs.

I’m now pursuing my Master’s in Digital Audience Strategy at @arizonastateuniversity, with plans to graduate in August 2025.

As much as I love Spice Up Your Social, that name is a mouthful. So, we’re in the middle of a rebrand and officially becoming Spicify!

It might seem like I’m the new girl on the block, but I’ve been in this industry for over 6 years—and I’ve loved every minute of it.

I don’t post much on my personal or business accounts because (like most social media managers) I pour everything into my clients.

But that’s about to change.
Prepare yourselves for some cringe worthy content 🫣
